<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>call boy • call man</xh5><p> <i>call boy—</i>1. a man who calls up actors in a theater for duty: Indignant denials were interrupted by the <u>call-boy</u> knocking on the door and calling for Second Act beginners. 2. a messenger on a steamer, in a hotel, etc.: He obtained summer work as a part-time messenger—a job referred to at that time as <u>call boy</u>. 3. a young male prostitute (who makes appointments by phone): Hustlers fall into two categories: the street variety and models (<u>call boys</u>).</p><p> <i>call man—</i>a man available for emergency call, such as a part-time fireman: The <u>call man</u> nearest to the emergency situation was dispatched, since only one person manned the fire station.</p> </entry>
